# NCBI genome catalog snapshot (~60MB) used as input to DetermineAccessionsDataframe_SpeciesGenus.py
# and DetermineEvolutionaryPaths.py. NOT reproducibly regeneratable: Download_NCBI_Genome_Summaries.sh
# pulls live from NCBI's `datasets summary genome taxon` and the catalog grows over time, so a fresh
# pull won't match the original April 2025 snapshot used in the analysis. Archived on Zenodo instead —
# see README for the DOI/link. Download it into
# ScriptsForAnalysis/SourmashAndANIb_Comparison/SpeciesGenusAnalysis/ before running the scripts below.
ScriptsForAnalysis/SourmashAndANIb_Comparison/SpeciesGenusAnalysis/fungi_genome_summary_Apr14_2025.json

# Derived from the Zenodo-archived fungi_genome_summary_Apr14_2025.json above via
# ScriptsForAnalysis/SourmashAndANIb_Comparison/SpeciesGenusAnalysis/Run_DetermineAccessionsDataframe.sh
# (DetermineAccessionsDataframe_SpeciesGenus.py hardcodes reading that exact json file, so it must be
# in place first - this script alone can't regenerate this file from scratch).
ScriptsForAnalysis/SourmashAndANIb_Comparison/SpeciesGenusAnalysis/SpeciesGenus_names.csv
